-- Egypt bourse says cancels Wednesday's EFG Hermes share transactions 
-- 
-- Thu Jun 05, 2014 02:49AM EDT
-- None



CAIRO, June 5 (Reuters) - Egypt's bourse has decided to cancel all Wednesday's transactions on financial group EFG Hermes <HRHO.CA> shares, which will open on Thursday at 13.17 Egyptian pounds ($1.84)day, it said in a statement.

Beltone Financial <BTFH.CA> and a group of investors including billionaire Naguib Sawiris are seeking to acquire a 20 percent stake in EFG Hermes, two sources familiar with the matter told Reuters. [ID:nL6N0OM0YF]